    &lt;Title&gt;No options for comments on the Emergency Department&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;The emergency department is not fit for purpose.  I have been there twice, accompanying someone else. It is an overcrowded rabbit warren with no signposts, powerless triage staff, 7 hour waiting times on hard seats, and no system for urgent assessment. The ambulances patients are given priority and take up all the beds, again without an assessment of need, as some people use ambulances as a taxi service.  I recommend that people call an ambulance if worried about their health. I drove the very sick person in,  instead of calling an ambulance, so we were ignored for too long. The whole area should be rebuilt. In the meantime, it should be properly managed. At least put some signs up.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
